value: 10th buds of trees, especially black currant bushes, very forward for this time of year. wild honeysuckle on south side of house in leaf.

the most severe of this winter, very appearance of a very cold night, 2pm heavens clear (0). 4pm bar 29.706, wind nw 6 temp fair about 18.0, 7pm bar 29.861 wind nw6, 9pm bar 29.941 wind nw6 and bright starlight. in my walk this afternoon,  i witnessed the largest snow drifts i have seen at any time in or about niagara.

prevailing winds were southerly as regards direction westerly as regards velocity. overcast 31 observations out of 72. clear 3, number of days wholly overcast wire.
